The Telegraph - Calcutta : Sports

 India to host 2011 Cup final 

Karachi: Bangladesh will host the opening ceremony of the 2011 World Cup while the final is set to be held in India, officials said Saturday. 

Bangladesh, India, Pakistan and Sri Lanka will co-host the event and a decision of boards of the four countries in this regard was final. 

Pakistan Cricket Board (PCB) director operations Abbas Zaidi said that India will host the final while the semi-finals would be held in Sri Lanka and Pakistan. 

Pakistan were keen on the final, but the BCCIs stand was that the rotation policy should stay in place ? India hosted the 1987 final while Pakistan the 1996 editions final. 

India are scheduled to host 22 matches, with Pakistan holding 16, Sri Lanka 9 and Bangladesh 6. (Agencies) 




